---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Services"
	description="Surveys, course mapping, and structural engineering advice to support drainage and sustainability projects on golf courses."
>
	<section class="section section--tight hero">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="eyebrow">Services</span>
			<h1>Surveys, maps, and structural engineering</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				Drainage and sustainability work is only as good as the information behind it. These
				supporting services make sure course interventions are targeted, recorded, and built to
				last.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="grid grid--2">
				<div class="card">
					<h3>Surveys &amp; Maps</h3>
					<p>
						Creating or updating course maps and drainage records so future work, yours or ours,
						is based on evidence, not memory.
					</p>
					<a href="/services/surveys-maps/">Learn more →</a>
				</div>
				<div class="card">
					<h3>Structures</h3>
					<p>
						Slope stability, constructional advice, and procurement support for bridges, culverts,
						and other course structures tied to drainage performance.
					</p>
					<a href="/services/structures/">Learn more →</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
